A rugged sea captain with the unescapable hook. He keeps a close eye on the sailors that scurry around the ship. From the man's demeanor he'd likely be the one to talk to if you were looking for passage.

Value.value: We'll make our own governin'! With blackjack and hookers!
Yeah, I think we'll be fine on our own. Even a West-born King didn't care about us.

Value.value: We're tired of bein' pushed around. Bet we can do a better job on our own out here. We don't need no king or furniture-leaders.
Ya got anything in yer pockets? Better check.
Mind yer business. We don't need outside "help".
We can take care of ourselves!

Dogma of Valkur: There is nothing more invigorating than challenging the elements. The feel of wind and spray on one's face and the deck pitching beneath one's feet is the greatest feeling in the world. If humankind is to expand its reach, daring men and women must defy the odds and dare the impossible. The thrill of exploration is sweeter than wine or rum. There is always risk, but without risk life is empty. Life is to be lived and damn the consequences. One's loyalties are first to one's mates, then to one's ship, and then to Valkur, who protects all sailors. Rely not on Valkur's hand to always extract you from difficulties, for such is coddling and leads to a lack of challenge and the room to grow. Rather, Valkur helps those actively solving their own problems by helping their plans work.

This cup is placed atop a make-shift shrine of sorts. People frequently sit on the planks as if they were a bench and have a drink and socialize, but despite this casual attitude, no one, not even the miscreants and troublemakers - ever steal the cup. Although it is sometimes used to drink from - only by citizens - it is always cleaned after and never taken from the shrine.

Outsiders often have a different experience, and anyone not of Southport who loiters around the shrine finds themselves "encouraged" to move along with hard stares. Gods forbid any outsiders try to touch or take the cup - such attempts are met with a surge of violent shouting and brandishing from the many street kids and adults alike.

== Laws of the Kingdom of Cetha ==


Admittance to Frontier's Rest

    1. To enter, you are not permitted to wear a helmet or hood or use any other method to conceal your identity. Head coverings may be worn after entrance is permitted.
    2. Weapons may be carried or sheathed in city limits, provided weapons are only used in self-defense or at the direction of local law enforcement.
    3. Kingdom personnel may stop you to verify your identity against banishment lists.
    --> 3. 1. Failure to comply with requests from official personnel will result in violation of Criminal Law, point 4.

----------------------------------------


Banishment from Frontier's Rest

    The following creatures are banished and will be killed on sight:
        - Orcs
        - Trolls
        - Undead
        - Yuan-Ti
        - Full-blooded Fiends
        - Gnolls

    1. Individuals listed on the Kingdom's separate banishment list will not be permitted entry.
    2. Only the Magistrate or royal family of Cetha may approve permanent banishment of individuals.
    3. Temporary banishment of 24 hours may be given by guards and official personnel of the Kingdom of Cetha.
    4. Individuals who have been banished have the right to request an appeal. Appeals will be observed by the Magistrate of Law.

----------------------------------------


Criminal Law

    1. Murder and Manslaughter.
    2. Assault.
    3. Thievery, Banditry, and Slavery.
    4. Disturbing the Public Safety and Peace.
    5. Harassment.
    6. Bribery, Extortion, and Blackmail.
    7. Public Indecency.
    8. Vandalism to Public or Private Property.


Spellcasting Law

    1. The casting of offensive spells is prohibited, except in defense of self or others, or for training purposes overseen by Kingdom personnel.
    2. Casting of defensive spells is permitted.
    3. Shapeshifting, either through magic or innate ability, into creatures listed on the banished lists is prohibited.
    --> 3. 1. The shapeshifting individual will be killed on sight.
    4. Summoned creatures may travel with their summoner.
    --> 4. 1. Summoned creatures that infringe on Criminal Law point 4 are prohibited, as determined by guard and official Kingdom personnel.
    --> 4. 2. Summoned creatures that are listed on the banished lists are prohibited and will be killed on sight.
    --> 4. 3. The summoner is responsible for all actions of the summoned creature, including any criminal actions.
